result.notes:
Full water quality monitoring data set from the Commonwealth Marine Economies 
Programme survey around Tarawa, Kiribati in March 2019.

This work was hosted and supported by the Kiribati Ministry of Lands, 
Environment and Development Environment and Conservation Division (MELAD-ECD), 
a list of collaborators is given in the attached readme file. The key 
parameters measured were: nutrients, chlorophyll, total suspended solids, E 
coli., intestinal Enterococci, vibrio and ESBL-producing bacteria (as a 
measure of antimicrobial resistance).
